CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper July 13, 1957, pg. 10, reads: "Emmanuel's New Edifice - The new Emmanuel Baptist Church, Rankin, will formally enter its new edifice on July 14, and will hold services each night up to July 21. The following pastors and their congregations will be featured: The Revs. O. C. Perkins, Herbert Wilkerson, C. H. Smith, J. W. Henderson and J. C. Martin. Speakers on the 21st will be B. H. Logan at 11 A. M., J. A. Williams, 3:30 P. M., and H. R. Williams at 7:30 P. M. The Rev. S. C. Taylor (inset) is pastor. - Harris Photos."
